{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5134067d-4e77-4365-86ce-bf0a6ae3ec4a","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, and the reason string appears in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6b764004-45a4-4160-8a35-e756922f1843","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":307,"requestId":"1BDB:1521A3:6BE5103:746BDF1:6A03D24C"},"id":"805a4493-258e-44e7-9bce-86629da70fb7","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:22:27.589Z","parentId":"0752853e-0ccc-41c9-8078-a5e9f4c430f0"}
